01/03/2009
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Former Prime Minister Manea Manescu, a close ally of communist dictator Nicolae Ceausescu, has died at the age of 92, local media reported on Saturday (February 28th). 
Manescu joined the Communist Party in 1944, holding various posts before becoming prime minister from 1974 until 1979. 
In February 1990, he was sentenced to life in prison for genocide. 
Later, his sentence was reduced and he was eventually released from prison for medical reasons. 
(Evenimentul Zilei, AFP - 28/02/09)
